No. 54, No. 391,

Misc.

Misc.

Nelms v. United States; and Dow, aka Corey v. Attorney General of the United States. Solicitor General Marshall, Assistant Attorney General Vinson and Beatrice Rosenberg for the United States, in opposition in both cases.

Motions for leave to file petitions for writs of habeas corpus denied.

Mr. Justice Marshall took no part in the consideration or decision of these motions.
